# Cloudflare Pages redirects.
#
# Cloudflare Pages keeps serving a path from an earlier deployment when the newest
# build no longer contains that file, so removing a page from the build is not enough
# to take it off the web. These rules retire such URLs explicitly.
#
# The demo/sample Journal article existed only to exercise the editorial blocks. It was
# deleted from Sanity, the seed, and the seed generator, so it can never be rebuilt —
# but the previously-deployed file lingered. Send it to the Journal rather than 404ing,
# so anyone holding the link (or an index entry) lands somewhere useful.
/journal/sample-a-morning-with-the-breath   /journal/   301
/journal/sample-a-morning-with-the-breath/  /journal/   301
